original: Laorin, Adde, förste trafikingenjör, Gö’teb’org, f. 3/9/10 i Sthlm av red. Adolf o. Elvira L. G. 34 ni. Maja Stjerna. Barn: Mats f. 37. — Stud:-ex. 29, stud. v. KTH 29-33. Anst. v. Stlilms gatukont. 34, Gbgs spårv. 34-35, stadsplanekont. i Gbg sed. 35, chef f. trafikavd. där. Utf. utredn. för bl. a. vägnät o. övriga trafikspörsmål i regionplanen f. Gbg m. omgivn., biltra-fikräkn. i Gbg, Borås o. Hälsingb., spårv itrafikräkn. i Gbg, Jönköp. o. Hälsingborg kalkyler f. samt försl. t. buss-resp. spårvägslinjenät i Karlskoga, Örebro, Eskilstuna o. Hälsingborg, teor. undersökn. av restider o. reskostn. m. m. för stadsbyggn :inst. v. KTH. Resor t. Danm. o. Berlin 32, Tyskl., Holl. o. Belg. 33, Paris o. London 37, Schweiz, Frankr. o. Ital. 38, Schweiz o. Engl. 47. Hobbies: friluftsliv, orien- ter., fjällfärder, kanotpaddling.
translated: Laorin, Adde, first traffic engineer, Gothenburg, b. 3/9/10 in Stockholm to editor Adolf and Elvira L. G. 34 née Maja Stjerna. Child: Mats b. 37. – Passed student examination 29, student at Royal Institute of Technology 29-33. Employed at Stockholm Street Planning Office 34, Gothenburg Tramways 34-35, City Planning Office in Gothenburg since 35, Head of Traffic Department there. Conducted investigations for, among others, road network and other traffic issues in the regional plan for Gothenburg and its surroundings, car traffic counting in Gothenburg, Borås, and Hälsingborg, tram traffic counting in Gothenburg, Jönköping, and Hälsingborg, calculations for bus and tram network proposals in Karlskoga, Örebro, Eskilstuna, and Hälsingborg, theoretical studies on travel times and travel costs etc. for urban planning institute at the Royal Institute of Technology. Travelled to Denmark and Berlin in 32, Germany, the Netherlands, and Belgium in 33, Paris and London in 37, Switzerland, France, and Italy in 38, Switzerland and England in 47. Hobbies: outdoor activities, orienteering, mountain trips, canoeing.
